news.title: Keystone Realtors' sales bookings up 22% to Rs 611 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: In volume terms, the Mumbai-based company said its sales bookings fell 16 per cent to 0.24 million square feet from 0.29 million square feet during the period under review.

news.title: Residents worry about infra and funds amidst Secunderabad Cantonment & GHMC merger
news.para: In its latest letter issued on June 28, this has been revised to “proprietary rights over assets meant for providing civic amenities and municipal services”.

news.title: Two years on, construction waste piles up in Gurugram's sector 47
news.para: For two years, a 6-acre plot in Gurgaon’s Sector 47, near Delhi Public School, faces illegal dumping, parking, and encroachment. Residents Virender Tyagi and Prateek Jain report health risks and dust pollution.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to repair 24 blocks of Kishanwadi housing scheme built in 2010
news.para: The notices were pasted on 28 of the 94 blocks in the housing scheme for the urban poor. The notices ask residents to vacate these houses and stay in them only after they are repaired.

news.title: China's Guangzhou R&F Properties receives winding-up petition
news.para: The petition on Trillion Glory, the unit in question, was filed by the Singapore-based private equity fund, which holds a 18% interest in the total outstanding loan amounting to $613.66 million, in a Hong Kong court.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body collects just Rs 463 crore property tax through OTS
news.para: As July 31 deadline comes closer, BBMP manages to collect just Rs 463 cr in taxes while Rs624.8 cr is still outstanding

news.title: Samsung R&D Institute-Bangalore renews office lease for five years
news.para: According to a lease renewal deed shared by analytics firm Propstack, the firm will pay an annual rent of ?50 crore, with a 5% yearly escalation. This translates to ?102 per square foot per month.

news.title: Noida authority may not allow construction up to purchasable FAR without permission
news.para: For instance, say a builder has been allotted 10,000sqm for a group housing project. If the approved layout says that the company can carry out construction on 5,000sqm, it means that the total ground area is 50%.

news.title: Mayfield Gardens' builder refuses to handover land to Gurugram civic body
news.para: According to MCG officials, the corporation is mandated by the department of town and country planning (DTCP) to take possession of 327-acre land belonging to the colony.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra's sales bookings up 36% to Rs 306 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: In a statement, Dhaval Ajmera, Director at Ajmera Realty & Infra India, said the company achieved robust growth of 36 per cent buoyed by the successful launch of its project 'Ajmera Vihara' at Bhandup in Mumbai.

news.title: Homebuyers being defrauded, uniform buyer-builder agreement necessary: SC
news.para: The top court was hearing a PIL filed by lawyer Ashwini Upadhyay in 2021, saying a model agreement was required to ensure transparency and fairness and to restrain builders and agents from indulging in unfair and restrictive trade practices.

news.title: Tata Realty secures Rs 825 crore from IFC to refinance IT park in Chennai
news.para: Ramanujan Intellion Park has achieved a complete reduction of emissions through renewables or carbon off-sets, saving more than 20 percent on water and embodied energy in materials while attaining over 42% percent energy savings on-site.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses to grant relief to 41 Vasai buildings facing demolition
news.para: A division bench of Justices M S Sonak and Kamal Khata, however, granted flat owners in the buildings time till September 30 to vacate the premises subject to submission of an undertaking to vacate.

news.title: MahaRERA acts against 628 projects for non-compliance with registration & QR code rules
news.para: To keep one’s investment secured, MahaRERA has appealed to homebuyers not to engage in transactions with housing projects without the mandatory RERA registration number.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance plans to raise up to $500 million through dollar-bond sale
news.para: Billionaire Ajay Piramal’s firm is in talks with a group of global investment banks to raise $300 million to $500 million via such notes with a tenor of three to five years, the people said, asking not to be identified as the discussion are private.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body to conduct 3D digital twin drone survey
news.para: The purpose of the drone survey is to create a comprehensive databank of the city that will assist the revenue, engineering, health, town planning, and other wings of the city corporation.

news.title: Panel to study BIS guidelines for uniform building code in Gautam Budh Nagar
news.para: Noida Authority has recently made this proposal, months after the director-general of BIS, Pramod Kumar Tiwari, urged it to include provisions of the Standardised Development and Building Regulation, 2023 (SDBR-2023) in its bylaws.

news.title: INH Mauritius to sell its 49% stake in JMFCS to JM Financial for about Rs 3,000 crore
news.para: INH Mauritius, an investment fund managed by Pandit, will sell 49% in JM Financial Credit Solutions (JMFCS) - the realty financing business - to Kampani's JM Financial in a deal valued at about Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: YEIDA withdraws plea at NCLAT against Ace Infracity bid for Three C Homes
news.para: Both YEIDA and Ace Infracity were in talks for settlement, while the matter was pending before the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT).

news.title: HDFC Capital to invest $2 billion in affordable housing segment by 2025 end
news.para: The world's largest affordable housing platform that counts ADIA as its key investor is in the process of achieving its medium-term goal of financing 1 million affordable homes in India through existing platforms set up with leading developers.
